The paper deals with kernelization, which is a topic in computational complexity and algorithms. The focus is on the Vertex Cover problem, which is a classic problem in graph theory and combinatorics. The paper also introduces and analyzes new graph classes, such as $d$-quasi-forests, $d$-quasi-bipartite graphs, and $d$-quasi-integral graphs, which are relevant to several subfields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and graph theory (cs.GT).
